%N A397230 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * AH(2*k,2)/k, where AH(k,2) = A119682(k)/A334580(k) is the k-th alternating harmonic (or skew-harmonic) number of order 2.
%H A397230 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.22, p. 426.
